    "data_flow": "1) Client submits order → Orchestrator creates saga instance (state: STARTED). 2) Orchestrator calls Order Service → createOrder → persists step result (orderId). 3) Orchestrator calls Inventory Service → reserveItems → persists step result (reservationId). 4) Orchestrator calls Payment Service → chargeCustomer → persists step result (paymentId). 5) Orchestrator calls Courier Service → assignCourier → persists step result (assignmentId). 6) All succeed → saga state: COMPLETED, Order status: CONFIRMED. On failure at any step N: orchestrator walks the compensation log in reverse from step N-1 down to step 1, calling each service's compensating action. Saga state: COMPENSATING → COMPENSATED. Each compensation is retried with backoff until success.",
