      "sacrifices": "Orchestrator is a coordination single point — must be highly available. Services are coupled to the orchestrator's command schema (though not to each other). Slightly more infrastructure than fire-and-forget events.",
      "alternatives_considered": ["Choreography saga — each service emits events and the next service reacts. Rejected because: compensation ordering becomes implicit and fragile across 4 services; debugging failures requires correlating events across all services; adding a step means modifying multiple services' event handlers."]
